Package: iftop
Source: iftop (1.0~pre4-4)
Version: 1.0~pre4-4+b1
Architecture: amd64
Maintainer: Markus Koschany <apo@debian.org>
Installed-Size: 94
Depends: libc6 (>= 2.7), libncurses6 (>= 6), libpcap0.8 (>= 0.9.8), libtinfo6 (>= 6)
Section: net
Priority: optional
Homepage: http://www.ex-parrot.com/~pdw/iftop/
Description: displays bandwidth usage information on an network interface
 iftop does for network usage what top(1) does for CPU usage. It listens to
 network traffic on a named interface and displays a table of current bandwidth
 usage by pairs of hosts. Handy for answering the question "Why is my Internet
 link so slow?".
